task.summary:
Ravikiran: Holidu-Challenge code commit To read the data from H2 database and index it to Elasticsearch, I'm making use of Elasticsearch Java API's Bulk API. Using an external framework like Logstash or Beats and configuring it with JDBC, the data can be read from the DB and indexed to Elasticsearch continuously. That approach is not taken here since it would require a one time manual intervention to setup Logstash/Beats.
The application supports search Apartment by Name/Type/Facility or a combination of the same. By default, all the apartments are shown on the screen, and will be further filtered based on the parameters chosen. The endpoint is /apartments to view all the apartments and apply a filter. The endpoint /apartments/:id is exposed as well, to fetch details of any particular Apartment. The same can be achieved by clicking on the Apartment Name in the table shown on /apartments
